main event: A group of airborne observers on Guam spotted several unidentified white, apparently burning objects with white smoke trails, moving at an estimated speed of 200-300 mph.
interesting points: The objects were first seen about 20 degrees above the horizon and moved higher in the sky.
One object left a very bright white trail that started pulsating just before burning out, while another object was a dull green light that fell vertically.
The observers included an aircraft commander and pilot who were both rated as 100% reliable.
The weather conditions were clear with scattered cumulus clouds and 15+ mile visibility.
The objects were observed for 10-15 minutes before apparently burning out.
sighted object: white, apparently burning objects with smoke trails
witnesses: airborne observers, including an aircraft commander and pilot
